# <type>(<scope>): <subject — under ~70 chars, active voice, no period>
#
# Conventional prefixes: feat | fix | docs | chore | refactor | test | build | ci
# Scope is optional and short (e.g. mem0, install, journal, kb-capture).
#
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# The body — write enough context that a future reader can understand
# the WHY without archaeology. Sections are optional; omit what's empty.
# Delete these instructional comments before committing.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Context
# What was the situation that prompted this work? Prior state,
# symptoms, motivating evidence. The "why do anything at all" section.

## Decisions
# What specific choices were made? What alternatives were considered
# and rejected? The "why this approach, not another" section.

## Chain of reasoning
# How did context → decisions? Concrete findings, diagnostics, logic.
# The "how did we know" section. Fine to include URLs, file:line refs,
# commit SHAs, or sample output here.

## Implementation
# Prose mirror of the diff at the level of "what changed where."
# Brief — the diff itself is the source of truth for line-level detail.

## Implications
# What does this change enable, prevent, or affect downstream?
# First-order consequences (direct). Second-order (indirect / future
# users). Third-order (systemic / emergent) when relevant.
# Note any required user actions (rotate a key, restart something,
# run a migration).

## References
# Related commits (short SHA + one-line purpose), docs paths,
# external URLs, issue/ticket numbers if tracked elsewhere.

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# When to use the full template vs a shorter form
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Use the full template when: architectural decisions; cross-cutting
#   fixes; investigations where the diagnostic path is valuable;
#   changes a future reader will want to reconstruct.
#
# Use a shorter form (subject + 1-paragraph body) when: typos;
#   formatting-only; lint fixes; trivial config bumps; incremental
#   commits within a feature arc whose context lives in the epic's
#   first commit.
#
# The template is a ceiling, not a floor. When empty sections outnumber
# filled ones, delete the template comments and write a short
# paragraph instead.
